Detect NA

Detect NA takes a tibble and return the number and share of missing values for each variable

detect_na(table)

Arguments

table
name of the input variable

Value

a tibble with 3 columns (variable, n_missing, share_missing)

Examples

read_excel(
path = system.file(
"extdata",
"DINSIC-Panorama_des_grands_projets_SI_20161116.xlsx",
package = "tricky")
) %>%
set_standard_names() %>%
detect_na()
